msgid "Conditions"
msgstr "Feltételek"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/contributing/code-style-guide/perl.xml:130
msgid ""
"Conditions can be quite complex and there can be \"chained\" conditions "
"(linked with logical 'or' or 'and' operations).  When coding for OTRS, you "
"have to be aware of several situations."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/contributing/code-style-guide/perl.xml:136
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"if ( $Condition1 && $Condition2 ) { ... }\n"
"\n"
"# instead of\n"
"\n"
"if ( $Condition and $Condition2 ) { ... }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/contributing/code-style-guide/perl.xml:134
msgid ""
"Perl Best Practices says, that high precedence operators ('&amp;&amp;' and "
"'||') shouldn't mixed up with low precedence operators ('and' and 'or').  To "
"avoid confusion, we always use the high precedence operators.  <placeholder "
"type=\"programlisting\" id=\"0\"/> This means that you have to be aware of "
"traps. Sometimes you need to use parenthesis to make clear what you want."
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/contributing/code-style-guide/perl.xml:150
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"if (\n"
"    $Condition1\n"
"    && $Condition2\n"
"    )\n"
"{ ... }\n"
"\n"
"# instead of\n"
"\n"
"if ( $Condition1\n"
"    && $Condition2\n"
"    )\n"
"{ ... }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: CDATA
#: en/content/contributing/code-style-guide/perl.xml:169
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"if (\n"
"    $XMLHash[0]->{otrs_stats}[1]{StatType}[1]{Content}\n"
"    && $XMLHash[0]->{otrs_stats}[1]{StatType}[1]{Content} eq 'static'\n"
"    )\n"
"{ ... }\n"
"\n"
"if ( $TemplateName eq 'AgentTicketCustomer' ) {\n"
"    ...\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"if (\n"
"    ( $Param{Section} eq 'Xaxis' || $Param{Section} eq 'All' )\n"
"    && $StatData{StatType} eq 'dynamic'\n"
"    )\n"
"{ ... }\n"
"\n"
"if (\n"
"    $Self->{TimeObject}->TimeStamp2SystemTime( String => $Cell->{TimeStop} )\n"
"    > $Self->{TimeObject}->TimeStamp2SystemTime(\n"
"        String => $ValueSeries{$Row}{$TimeStop}\n"
"    )\n"
"    || $Self->{TimeObject}->TimeStamp2SystemTime( String => $Cell->{TimeStart} )\n"
"    < $Self->{TimeObject}->TimeStamp2SystemTime(\n"
"        String => $ValueSeries{$Row}{$TimeStart}\n"
"    )\n"
"    )\n"
"{ ... }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/contributing/code-style-guide/perl.xml:148
msgid ""
"If you have long conditions (line is longer than 120 characters over all), "
"you have to break it in several lines.  And the start of the conditions is "
"in a new line ( not in the line of the 'if').  <placeholder type="
"\"programlisting\" id=\"0\"/> Also note, that the right parenthesis is in a "
"line on its own and the left curly bracket is also in a new line an with the "
"same indentation as the 'if'.  The operators are at the beginning of a new "
"line! The subsequent examples show how to do it...  <placeholder type="
"\"programlisting\" id=\"1\"/>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><section><title>
